# AucoBot monorepo

Read first: `aucobot/docs/monorepoplan.md`, `aucobot/docs/monorepo-diagram.md` (section matching the task).

## Folder roles

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `aucobot/apps/api` | Nest wiring, controllers, DTOs, guards — **thin** |
| `aucobot/apps/web` | Next.js UI |
| `aucobot/packages/*` | Shared libs (OSS + cloud import contracts) |
| Sibling `cloud/` repo (`../cloud/*`) | Hosted cloud only — **do not** import into OSS apps |
| `aucobot/deploy/` | OSS compose + Dockerfiles (api/web) |
| Gateway/postgres | **Pull images** — not vendored in repo |

## Forbidden without explicit user ask

- New top-level folder, rename `apps/` / `packages/` / `cloud/`
- New npm dependency (root or package) without reason
- Abstractions used once (base class, factory, “future” config)
- Cloud logic (docker spawn, billing) in `packages/` OSS or `apps/api` long-term
- `workers/openclaw` inside `aucobot/` — use Hub image + `../openclaw-worker/` fork
- Drive-by refactors, formatting, or “cleanup” outside task scope
- New markdown docs unless user requested

## Task discipline

1. One task → one package **or** one app layer; small diff.
2. **Move/copy** existing code before rewriting architecture.
3. State verify command and run it before finishing.

## Verify (from `aucobot/`)

```bash
pnpm --filter @aucobot/runtime-contracts build   # if runtime touched
pnpm --filter @aucobot/runtime-oss build
pnpm --filter @aucobot/api build
pnpm --filter @aucobot/web build                 # if web touched
```

Compose E2E: `docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.yml up -d --build`

## Runtime placement

- Interfaces → `packages/runtime-contracts`
- OSS gateway URL/health → `packages/runtime-oss`
- Cloud spawn → `@aucobot-cloud/fleet` in sibling `cloud/` repo — **never** `runtime-oss`
